summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingGive BackFresh's Black Tea Anti-Aging Eye Cream with Retinol-Alternative BT Matrix with ceramide addresses aging skin by visibly firming the eye area, smoothing crows feet, and improving dark circles with vitamin c.
details: DetailsBenefitsVisibly improves dark circles for brighter eyesVisibly firms eye area & smoothes wrinklesOphthalmologist testedKey IngredientsBT Matrix with retinol-like strength* corrects signs of aging *ex vivo studies on BT Matrix ingredients; this product does not contain retinolVitamin C helps to brighten the look of dark circlesWild ginger extract helps to reduce the look of dark circles & eye bagsCeramide NP helps strengthen the skin barrierHyaluronic acid attracts and maintains moistureResearch ResultsAfter 8 weeks, consumers saw8x visibly improved dark circles*8x firmer eye area**8x smoother crow's feet**observed results, self-assessment by scoring, 32 subjects, comparing results from 1st application to after 8 weeksItem 2620775How To UseAfter cleansing, smooth onto entire eye area, morning and night.IngredientsAqua (water), Glycerin, Squalane, Propylene Glycol Dicaprylate/dicaprate, Butylene Glycol, Cetearyl Alcohol, Behenyl Behenate, Pentylene Glycol, Polyglycerin-6, C10-18 Triglycerides, Silica, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Nephelium Lappaceum Leaf Extract, Zingiber Zerumbet Extract, Tocopherol, Cetearyl Glucoside, Stearalkonium Hectorite, Sodium Polyacrylate, Polyglycerin-3, Pullulan, Maltodextrin, Propanediol, Sodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Parfum (fragrance), Propylene Carbonate, Acrylates/c10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Ascorbyl Tetraisopalmitate, Ceramide Np, Sodium Hyaluronate, Hydroxyacetophenone, Adenosine, Sodium Hydroxide, Biosaccharide Gum-2, Caramel, Sodium Benzoate, Chlorphenesin, Potassium Sorbate, Linalool, Citronellol, Geraniol \<19146\>.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Absolutely love this product
reviews.comments: I love the way it leaves my eyes looking. This is my second time buying and I also got one for my daughter

reviews.headline: I don't like it
reviews.comments: No one mentiones the horrific pilling of products on yhr skin. It feels nice and fresh when first applying but after an hour the piling starts and its truly such an unpleasant feeling and look under the eyes.

reviews.headline: Worth It Splurge
reviews.comments: I tend to go for the cheapest products I know will work skincare wise.  Lots of one-ingredient wait-and-see type of use.  I loved seeing the before and afters both provided by the company and in the reviews here as that gave me a lot more confidence that the product would do what it said (especially at $70+).  What I'm here to say is that the immediate result is very distinct.  Obviously the long term use will actually reverse some of my allergy eyes (I should've listened to my mum about not rubbing my eyes!)  The hydration is super lightweight while effective and there's an immediate difference as soon as it soaks in.  I also have very sensitive skin and this product has no burning or other sensations I get with ingredients I'm sensitive to.  I'm just waiting for my reusable eye masks to come in the mail and I'll be all set on my skincare routine.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I love this eye cream. I have very dry, fragile, sensitive skin around my eyes and most products contain retinol or other ingredients which cause my skin to redden, flake, peel and even bleed.  This product is thick and moisturizing, with a "retinol-alternative" which does not bother my sensitive skin. It also seems to reduce puffiness and dark circles, but my main reason for using it is the moisturizing effects. After the eye cream I was using for 30 years was discontinued, I tried about 25 different products until I finally found this one. I hope they keep it available for the next 30 years! I am a loyal customer.

reviews.headline: A let down
reviews.comments: After many great reviews, most based on receiving a free product I discovered I would never buy again. The product is thick to the point when applying pretty much tugs on your delicate eye skin plus no matter how little or how moisturized my eye area is this never actually absorbs. It always pills. So its a waste of product since its not actually absorbing. For the price of this there is no reason on top of the negatives to repurchase.

reviews.headline: Finally!
reviews.comments: I finally found a eye cream that does what it state's it does. Soaks into my skin beautifully and you see a difference immediately.

reviews.headline: Clumpy under makeup
reviews.comments: I purchased this eye cream after reading such great reviews, but I wish I had stuck with my normal cream. This is fine for nighttime when going to bed, but it does not go under makeup well! I even waited several minutes after applying to make sure it had fully absorbed. As soon as I put on my foundation or tinted moisturizer, it clumps and flakes. I literally have to pull pieces of it off my face, and what is left just makes my undereye area look dry and flaky. Disappointing.

reviews.headline: Yes, I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: I like the soft and textured the this product in my skin

reviews.headline: Like the product so far but disappointed
reviews.comments: Like the product so far. Was disappointed that the eye cream was half filled I believe to an air pocket. Ulta had told me I needed to contact the company! Which I guess leads me to believe it is probably easier to just order directly and take the middle man. I guess that a true sign that brick and mortar and a thing of the past!ü§∑üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

reviews.headline: Best eye cream on the market for many reasons
reviews.comments: first off, I'm all about sustainability. using products like fresh eliminates microplastics from my routine and also uses clean ingredients. I love using this day and night, and a little goes a long way! I have sensitive skin, and have always found this product soothing. It is also amazing for makeup prep. I used to cheap out on my eye cream, but don't let the price stop you. This small container easily lasts 5 months and that's because my bf started using it too when he saw how well it enhances my skin!

reviews.headline: Black circle miracle!!!
reviews.comments: I very rarely write reviews but I just had to tell anyone with dark circles, this stuff really works! I truly had no idea just how good it was until i ran out. I really couldn't justify the cost to reorder.  However, within a few weeks the black circles returned and it was then that I realized I will never be without this eye cream again. It doesn't happen overnight, but it does happen. Be patient. It's worth it.

reviews.headline: Bad reaction
reviews.comments: My second day and woke up with my eye puffy , and peeling and dry. I beleive I got a bad reaction to this cream. Im so sad bechase of all the food reviews

reviews.headline: Great under eye and eyelid treatment!
reviews.comments: Great moisturizing undereye as well as Eyelid treatment. Surprised you can use all around the eye-but love that, as many other products are only under the eye. It is very rich, and only need a small amount. Will be buying more in a few months when this runs out1 FRESH is a great brand!

reviews.headline: It works.
reviews.comments: Im forever mad that this product works so well. It's expensive. I'm trying to hold onto some semblance of youth while being a teacher. This keeps my eyes from looking exhausted and minimizes the sun damage. Its far to expensive but worth it unfortunately.

reviews.headline: Perfect Eye Cream
reviews.comments: I am over 40 and have been looking for an eye cream that would reduce my wrinkles.  I was at Ulta and someone suggested I try this brand and I am so glad I did. My under eye skin is nourished and wrinkles reduced.

reviews.headline: Would recommend!
reviews.comments: I had a sample size of this eye cream, not gifted by fresh, and it lasted me a really long time! A little bit goes along way and I didn't find it to be too heavy or greasy. I did specifically use it at night and woke up with less dark circles around my eyes. I didn't notice any scents in particular but I'm also not too sensitive to scents.

reviews.headline: Must have!
reviews.comments:
Bought this on our road trip when I noticed my under eye dark circles and puffiness worsened. Was
Pleasantly surprised to see that this product was extremely effective within one week. Wish i would have taken before and after photos.

reviews.headline: Nope
reviews.comments:
I've literally only used this once and I already know it needs to be returned. It's a very thick cream which is what i was looking for, but it left my skin feeling even more dry within a couple minutes. The fragrance is also insanely strong which became irritating. This morning I woke up with milia as well. I really wanted to like this because all other eye creams I've used in the past changed their ingredients and caused irritation. 
Starting to lose hope on finding something that works.

reviews.headline: Not for me, I reacted poorly to this product
reviews.comments:
I used this cream nightly for a few weeks and I knew it would take time to see any results. I was trying to minimize fine lines and improve the look of dark circles. My skin is quite sensitive so retinol creams are too strong, I thought this cream would be a good alternative. I ended up getting puffiness and dryness under my eyes after a few weeks, so sadly I needed to stop using the product. 

On a positive note, the cream has a nice scent to it and it's easy to apply.

reviews.headline: Best I have used
reviews.comments:
I am 75 and started with some puffiness and brownish under eyes. 
After using multiple products, I have hit the jackpot. Love what this producs does. A little pricy for me, but worth it.  
I don't even need to use concealer anymore. Huge benefit!!

faceoff_positive.comments: I was gifted this FRESH Black Tea Age Renewal Eye Cream complimentary from FRESH and Skeepers in exchange of my honest opinion. I liked this eye cream. I liked the fact that under my eyes felt more moisturized then they have been in awhile. This eye cream targets all zones of the eye area to visibly smooth wrinkles, improve the look of firmness and brighten. You use this after you cleanse your face and you use it morning and night. This Age Renewal Eye Cream also can be used between eyebrows to help smooth the '11' lines. Which to me is a + in my book. I would definitely recommend this Age Renewal Eye Cream by FRESH to anyone who wants or needs help under their eyes.
faceoff_positive.headline: AGE RENEWAL EYE CREAM

faceoff_negative.comments: I have been using the black tea fresh eye cream for OVER 5 YEARS! I am very disappointed in their formula change. Their previous version was the Age Delay Eye Cream. Their old version did not have propanediol and this new version does. It is a bummer because I stocked up over the holidays and will be on the hunt for a new eye cream. The new formula pills, sits on top of my under eyes and does not work well under make up at all. I tried under eye concealers from Benefit, bobbi brown, nars, charlotte tilbury, none of them work with this new eye cream. Please fresh - bring back the old formula!!
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointed in formula change
